Body: Extra Credit has been added to  WISERICO tracker    Vote for the Extra Credit on WISERICO and follow Extra Credit on the  media platforms:  Telegram Twitter Facebook Medium   We at Extra Credit, are the first company to start empowering people to learn about cryptocurrencies. It is a twofold effort with Bitcoin Homework, the new venture combines blockchain technology with educational programs designed to teach people about cryptocurrencies, even as they share in the digital payment for perhaps the first time. Extra Credit Extra Credit was created with the average working-class person in-mind; people who have no, or very little knowledge of CryptoCurrency. Our vision is to empower everyone with the knowledge required to invest and manage their CryptoCurrencies with ease. This means that anyone can participate in ExtraCredit, with or without past CryptoCurrency experience. Our Team Our Team Extra Credit brings together a team of 10 members, dedicated to teaching our users all they need to know about CryptoCurrencies. Should you have any questions, you can usually reach one of our team via the small chat button at the bottom right of our page. To contact any of our team directly, checkout our Team Section. Author: BitcoinHomework
Title: [ANN] üçé BitcoinHomework ‚≠ê ExtraCredit (XTRA) üçé Exchange SOON! ‚≠ê
Body: Quote from: BitcoinHomework on January 22, 2018, 08:40:33 AM Quote from: OgNasty on December 23, 2017, 09:47:45 PM Quote from: ChrisPontius on December 23, 2017, 09:07:32 PM   Thank you for asking this question so I can be clear about my involvement.  I am an advisor to BitcoinHomework, which means I have no control over the project.  However, I am asked to be an advisor for ICOs quite often and I nearly always decline.  BitcoinHomework convinced me to my satisfaction that a great deal of time/money has been invested in this project, it will provide a beneficial service to the community, and has a high probability of being listed on some of the larger altcoin exchanges.  Answering your question; No, you shouldn't run and buy this because I am an advisor.  However, it should make you take a closer look, as I believe this project has potential to positively effect the community and would personally like to see it succeed for that reason.

This courses are important to help especially the newbies find their feet on the ground and be able to differentiate scam from real projects and investment, real growth and pumps, etc.  It will be beneficial to the whole cryptocurrency echo system because one scammed newbie can spread FUD enough to drag prizes down for a while thereby stiffling the growth of cryptocurrency generally and the subsequent development that requires these funds.  Every crypto enthusiast is supposed to rally round this project and support it in anyway we can

Otherwise if they have to learn from other sources on how to buy and invest cryptos, then why would they take your course in the first place?  Secondly, by your numbers, you want to raise a $40M amount. That's a very big amount. Where do you intend to spend that money on? Just launching the platform? For all other activities you are already spending the remaining 200M tokens.  Lastly no links for the team members. One of the advisor having non human face!  But otherwise the project seems to have good potential for non crypto people and techies who want to learn about blockchain in depth.

Author: BitcoinHomework
Title: [ANN] üçé BitcoinHomework ‚≠ê ExtraCredit (XTRA) üçé Exchange SOON! ‚≠ê
Body: BitcoinHomework - Cryptocurrency Wallet Introduction - Lesson # 1     We at Extra Credit, are the first company to start empowering people to learn about cryptocurrencies. It is a twofold effort with Bitcoin Homework, the new venture combines blockchain technology with educational programs designed to teach people about cryptocurrencies, even as they share in the digital payment for perhaps the first time.  Extra Credit is a new website that has laid out an ambitious roadmap for the following year and more; it is aimed at developing the way people learn about cryptocurrencies. There is a one-stop location where any questions can be answered; and people can learn how to invest in the technology so as not to miss out on its stunning potential.  They can test their progress of learning with our weekly quizzes, which help them achieve the most benefits from their efforts.  Very soon Extra Credit and Bitcoin Homework will be introducing a mobile app, allowing students to learn about cryptocurrencies on their phone or tablet. The end of 2018 brings, even more developments, including the development of an online podcast for further learning and an innovative Open Source platform, which will open the Extra Credit programs up to any college or educational institution with the foresight to adopt them.  We really hope you could help promote our new venture. Author: OgNasty
Title: [ANN] üçé BitcoinHomework ‚≠ê ExtraCredit (XTRA) üçé Exchange SOON! ‚≠ê
Body: Thank you for asking this question so I can be clear about my involvement.  I am an advisor to BitcoinHomework, which means I have no control over the project.  However, I am asked to be an advisor for ICOs quite often and I nearly always decline.  BitcoinHomework convinced me to my satisfaction that a great deal of time/money has been invested in this project, it will provide a beneficial service to the community, and has a high probability of being listed on some of the larger altcoin exchanges.  Answering your question; No, you shouldn't run and buy this because I am an advisor.  However, it should make you take a closer look, as I believe this project has potential to positively effect the community and would personally like to see it succeed for that reason.
